BoolFalse: zero the memory of a given register
BoolTrue: set a given register to false
Copy: set a given register to true
Increment: copy the content of one register to another
NotEquals: fill a bool register with the result of (A == B)
JumpAbsolute: fill a bool register with the result of (A != B)
JumpForward: jump to an absolute instruction index
JumpBackward: jump forwards given a relative instruction index offset
JumpAbsoluteIf: jump backwards given a relative instruction index offset
JumpForwardIf: jump to an absolute instruction index based on a condition register
JumpBackwardIf: jump forwards given a relative instruction index offset based on a condition register
ChangeType: jump backwards given a relative instruction index offset based on a condition register
Exit: change the type of a register (deprecated)
EndBlock: begins a new memory slice / block
ArrayReset: ends the last memory slice / block
ArrayGetNum: (DEPRECATED) clears an array and resets its content
ArraySetNum: (DEPRECATED) reads and returns the size of an array (binary op, in array, out int32)
ArrayGetAtIndex: (DEPRECATED) resizes an array (binary op, in out array, in int32)
ArraySetAtIndex: (DEPRECATED) returns an array element by index (ternary op, in array, in int32, out element)
ArrayAdd: (DEPRECATED) sets an array element by index (ternary op, in out array, in int32, in element)
ArrayInsert: (DEPRECATED) adds an element to an array (ternary op, in out array, in element, out int32 index)
ArrayRemove: (DEPRECATED) inserts an element to an array (ternary op, in out array, in int32, in element)
ArrayFind: (DEPRECATED) removes an element from an array (binary op, in out array, in inindex)
ArrayAppend: (DEPRECATED) finds and returns the index of an element (quaternery op, in array, in element, out int32 index, out bool success)
ArrayClone: (DEPRECATED) appends an array to another (binary op, in out array, in array)
ArrayIterator: (DEPRECATED) clones an array (binary op, in array, out array)
ArrayUnion: (DEPRECATED) iterates over an array (senary op, in array, out element, out index, out count, out ratio, out continue)
ArrayDifference: (DEPRECATED) merges two arrays while avoiding duplicates (binary op, in out array, in other array)
ArrayIntersection: (DEPRECATED) returns a new array containing elements only found in one array (ternary op, in array, in array, out result)
ArrayReverse: (DEPRECATED) returns a new array containing elements found in both of the input arrays (ternary op, in array, in array, out result)
InvokeEntry: (DEPRECATED) returns the reverse of the input array (unary op, in out array)
JumpToBranch: invokes an entry from the entry list
Execute: jumps to a branch based on a name operand
RunInstructions: single execute op (formerly Execute_0_Operands to Execute_64_Operands)
Invalid: runs a set of instructions lazily
FirstArrayOpCode: ends the last memory slice / block
LastArrayOpCode: (DEPRECATED) returns a new array containing elements found in both of the input arrays (ternary op, in array, in array, out result)
